A4.text: They are the dibenzazepines (imipramine, desipramine, clomipramine, trimipramine, lofepramine).

A5.text: They are the dibenzocycloheptadienes (amitriptyline, nortriptyline, protriptyline, butriptyline).

A6.text: Imipramine was the first TCA to be developed (by Ciba).

A7.text: Other tertiary amine TCAs include amitriptyline, clomipramine, dosulepin (dothiepin), doxepin, and trimipramine.

A8.text: Amitriptyline is a tricyclic antidepressant primarily used to treat major depressive disorder

A9.text: Nortriptyline reaches 10% higher level in the blood plasma than the parent drug amitriptyline
